Program: Omnibus
Title: Shakespeare, The World he Knew
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376kt4
Last Broadcast Date: 03 May 1994
A look at who would have been in the audience watching Shakespeare's plays in the Globe Theatre in Elizabethan England and what they might have believed and felt about the world. Contributors include Charles Nicholl and David Starkey.